Key Match Events: Jackson Chourio delivered the single that opened the door to a five-run inning
William Contreras hit a Statcast-projected 435-foot two-run shot to cap a rally
Freddy Peralta struck out eight and allowed two hits in six scoreless innings
Miscellaneous Highlights: The panel that Chourio's home run took out on the team's gigantic new scoreboard had been replaced, and a digital marker of Chourio's clout was added in the form of a baseball with his No. 11
Others: Andruw Monasterio and Sal Frelick each worked walks in the fifth inning
Blake Perkins followed with a two-run double
